The article is a statement by the President on World Humanitarian Day. The President reflects on the terrorist attack on the UN Headquarters in Baghdad seven years ago, which highlighted the dangers faced by unarmed humanitarians around the world. The international community has designated August 19 as World Humanitarian Day to honor these individuals who live and work in dangerous and difficult places, providing life-sustaining support to millions. The article also mentions the recent efforts of humanitarian aid workers in Haiti, Pakistan, Sudan, and Afghanistan. However, it also mourns the losses of humanitarian workers who have been targeted and emphasizes the need for their safety and the pursuit of humanitarian goals.